briefdescription.para: This type is used to act upon the value of common item attributes. If an "act" attribute (a type with the "act" prefix) has no value assigned, it is ignored. If it has a value, then that attribute on the target item(s) assume(s) that stated value when an attached Boolean condition evaluates to true. The attached condition may be an "If" statement or any expression that evaluates to a Boolean value.
